DataMetricsOutputInfo¶

class orbitpy.datametricscalculator.DataMetricsOutputInfo(spacecraftId=None, instruId=None, modeId=None, accessFile=None, dataMetricsFile=None, startDate=None, duration=None, _id=None)[source]¶
Class to hold information about the results of the data-metrics calculation. An object of this class is returned upon the execution

of the data metrics calculator.

Variables

  • spacecraftId (str or int) – Spacecraft identifier.

  • accessFile (str) – File (filename with path) where the access data is saved.

  • dataMetricsFile (str) – File (filename with path) where the data-metrics data is saved.

  • startDate (float) – Time start for the data-metrics calculation in Julian Date UT1.

  • duration (float) – Time duration over which data-metrics was calculated in days.

  • _id (str or int) – Unique identifier.

Parameters

  • instruId (str (or) int) – Sensor identifier.

  • modeId (str (or) int) – Mode identifier.
